body: $SBLK is bullishly clearing its 10-week moving average. The stock showed strength during a broad pullback in transport names and the RS line is turning higher again. The relative strength line has been regrouping after a bullish run from mid-January until early March. The fact it found buyers near the 50-day moving average is a good sign.
Star Bulk Carriers is based in Greece and Cyprus. It operates a fleet of around 130 vessels. It taps the market for dry bulk commodities
column3: minerals and grain as well as bauxite
column4: fertilizers and steel products. Management expects the firm to benefit from a reopening global economy.
